CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper May 14, 1966, pg. 9A, reads: "'SHAPP - FOR - GOV' HEADQUARTERS - A Homewood - Brushton Shapp-for-Governor Headquarters, was opened at 806 N. Homewood Ave. last Saturday, with hundreds of well-wishers dropping in to inspect the new quarters. Typical of those who took part in the opening day ceremonies were these people shown posing for the photographer. Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of men and women standing outside campaign headquarters for Milton Shapp for Governor of Pennsylvania, 806 North Homewood Avenue, Homewood
